    "Major challenges are the extreme diversity of both the epitope and paratope sequence spaces to sample 185, 186, the cross-reactivity of epitope-paratope interactions, especially for T cells 187, 188, and their conformational diversity, with multiple binding modes even for the same target 189.",
    "Assays sampling epitope-paratope binding pairs in a high-throughput fashion are lacking, already at the sequence level, and the available sequence data often consist only of a single chain.",
    "Available structural data, as mentioned, are even sparser.",
    "By way of example, solved structures of antibodies to date amount to a few thousands (7967 on the SabDab database 26) and the ones of TCRs to a few hundreds (605 on the STCRDab database 190).",
    "Ad hoc ML strategies can mitigate in part the problem of scarcity of data on epitope-paratope interactions by modeling them as particular instances of general protein-protein interactions, for which more data are available."
